{"abstract":[{"text":"Create your first macOS virtual machine in minutes.","type":"text"}],"sections":[],"metadata":{"role":"collectionGroup","title":"Getting Started with Spooktacular","roleHeading":"API Collection","modules":[{"name":"SpooktacularKit"}]},"topicSections":[{"anchor":"Core-Types","title":"Core Types","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineBundle","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachine"]},{"anchor":"Configuration","title":"Configuration","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineConfiguration","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/NetworkMode","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode"]},{"anchor":"Guides","title":"Guides","identifiers":["doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CLIReference","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/GitHubActionsGuide","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide"]}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","level":2,"anchor":"Overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Spooktacular runs macOS virtual machines on Apple Silicon using","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"Apple’s Virtualization framework. You interact with it through the","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"GUI app or the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" CLI — both backed by the same","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit","type":"reference","isActive":true},{"text":" library. A Kubernetes operator is planned for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"a future release.","type":"text"}]},{"name":"Important","type":"aside","style":"important","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"You need an Apple Silicon Mac (M1 or later) running"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"macOS 14.0 (Sonoma) or later. Each VM requires at least 20 GB of"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"free disk space and 4 CPU cores (see"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/VirtualMachineSpecification\/minimumCPUCount","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":")."}]}]},{"text":"Creating a VM with the CLI","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-CLI"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"Install Spooktacular and create a VM from the latest compatible IPSW:","type":"text"}]},{"type":"codeListing","code":["# Install via Homebrew","brew install --cask spooktacular","","# Create from the latest compatible IPSW","spook create my-vm --from-ipsw latest","","# Or specify custom hardware resources","spook create runner --cpu 8 --memory 16 --disk 100"],"syntax":"bash"},{"name":"Note","type":"aside","style":"note","content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"IPSW installation takes 10–20 minutes per VM. For faster"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"text":"deployment, create a base VM once, then use ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook clone","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"instant copies.","type":"text"}]}]},{"text":"Creating a VM with the GUI","type":"heading","level":3,"anchor":"Creating-a-VM-with-the-GUI"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Open Spooktacular."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click the "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"+","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":" button or press "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Cmd+N","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Enter a name and adjust hardware settings."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Click "},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Create","type":"text"}],"type":"strong"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"orderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The app downloads the latest compatible macOS IPSW and installs it","type":"text"},{"text":" ","type":"text"},{"text":"into a new VM bundle.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Managing-VMs","level":3,"text":"Managing VMs"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the ","type":"text"},{"code":"spook","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" CLI for day-to-day VM management:","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["# List all VMs","spook list","","# Start a VM (opens display window)","spook start my-vm","","# Start headless (for CI runners and servers)","spook start my-vm --headless","","# Clone instantly using APFS copy-on-write","spook clone my-vm runner-01","","# Show VM configuration","spook get my-vm","","# Delete a VM permanently","spook delete my-vm --force"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Apple Silicon supports a maximum of 2 concurrent VMs"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"per host. Attempting to start a third VM fails. See"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"isActive":true,"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/CapacityCheck"},{"text":" for details.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}],"type":"aside","style":"important","name":"Important"},{"anchor":"Provisioning-with-User-Data-Scripts","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"Provisioning with User-Data Scripts"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Automate VM setup by running a shell script after boot via SSH:"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"code":["spook start runner --headless \\","    --user-data ~\/setup.sh \\","    --provision ssh \\","    --ssh-user admin"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"bash"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ssh"},{"type":"text","text":" mode waits for the VM to boot, discovers its IP, connects"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"via SSH, and executes your script with real-time output streaming."},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"Disk-inject provisioning (zero-touch, no SSH required) is in"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"progress. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/ProvisioningMode","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for provisioning strategies and"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"doc:Provisioning"},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed guidance."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"EC2-Mac-Setup","level":3,"type":"heading","text":"EC2 Mac Setup"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Deploy Spooktacular on AWS EC2 Mac instances to double your CI"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"capacity. Install Spooktacular, create VMs from IPSW, clone"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"configured bases, and start runners with SSH provisioning."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/EC2MacDeployment","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for detailed EC2 Mac configuration."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"A Kubernetes operator (MacOSVM CRD) is planned for a future"},{"type":"text","text":" "},{"type":"text","text":"release. See "},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SpooktacularKit\/documentation\/SpooktacularKit\/KubernetesGuide","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" for the planned architecture.